    "summary": "After almost 40 years Oc\u00e9/Canon in many different functions in technical, business and people development, I decided to enjoy an early retirement, to be able to bike long distances, learn and share my stories and experiences to anybody with a growth mindset for the benefit of their own personal and wished career development.\n\nLife is like a long distance bike ride. During my rides Transalps, to Santiago de Compostela and to Rome, I've experienced what resilience, perseverance and willpower really mean, and what it takes in practice - lifepower. I came to the understanding that many lessons are directly applicable and useful in our private, professional and business lives. \nHappy to share my stories, experiences and lessons. \n\n\"Whatever you do, get the best out of yourself, involve friends, do good to others.\"\nMore than just a phrase - I've been in the arena. \n\nMy passion is to inspire others to get the best out of themselves. \nMy ambition is to be a good human. \n\nProfessional experiences: \nPeople and Leadership Development\nInternational Marketing\nBusiness Development\nLogistics and Business Operations\nSales and Sales Management\nCorporate Strategy & Product Planning\nEngineering, Research & Development\n\nSpecialties: \nLong Distance Biking - FLIPFLOP Mindset\nChange - Challenges & Opportunities\nLeadership - Vulnerability\nGrow Performance in Sales\nGROW - Coaching for Performance",
